<Author>prettygirl
<Content>Crazy about the Hotel Belgica My husband I stayed at the Belgica for 3 nights during a business/vacation trip to Ponce. The personnel at the hotel is very warm and friendly (like family)...especially Maria (the daytime clerk) while we were there. She was helpful in recommending restaurants, give us directions to other towns and took the time to share some of the culture of Ponce. The hotel is OK for a short stay (no pool). However, if you are looking for a clean room with a great view of the town, this is the hotel for you. You cannot beat the price per night and they also offer a continental breakfast. There are several other cafes and resturants for full breakfasts and also lunch and dinner. We will be returning to Ponce very shortly and will again stay at the Belgica. Oh, by the way, if you are a couple, ask for room #19...it has a balconey and a wonderful view of the city. Can be a little noisey if you are a light sleeper. However, it is worth it...spacious room, modern bath and great bed!! 
