<Content>Beautiful Quaint Place in Ponce My husband and I had a good experience at the Belgica Hotel. We were there for one night from May 22-23. We arrived almost 10pm to check in, and the lady at the front desk was very nice. She was not able to direct us properly to the hotel when we called earlier to ask for directions, but, she turned out to be so apologetic, sincere, and helpful afterall wtih settling us in, that we did not even think of the inconvenience we had driving to the hotel. The facilities were excellent as well. We had a balcony, had a good view of the street and the quaint buildings. The bed, the sheets, the sink, the toilet, the TV, the whole room was beautiful. I love the preserved windows and trimmings of the room. They even had breakfast in the morning. Personnel were polite. Hotel was very clean. VERY NICE! 
