<Content>Do not miss this one. Went to visit historic Ponce just this week. First the only problem with Ponce is that all the highways are doing construction. Once you find the Hotel Belgica it will be worth all the wait. You walk into this historic old building in literally the center of ponce. Dont stay at this hotel if you are looking for the most up to date services. Rooms dont have phones, there is no pool, and there is no elevator. This hotel is truly for people who like old world charm at very cheap prices. Emma and Joel are great and they will give you detailed maps of what to do. Beware though that typical spanish restaurants close very early so make sure you eat a big lunch. My personal recommendation is the restaurant literally across the street. Dont remember the name but its the only thing across the street. Enjoy Ponce 
