<Content>Nice place near all Found the place as reviewed. An older, adequately maintained property that is within 20 yds of Ponce's main square. No elevator so you will be carrying your own bags up marble staircases. Take an inner room as it is quieter, but each floor has a common veranda which you can use at will.Friendly. helpful staff who allowed us to park right in front of the hotel rather than have to use the public parking lot which is a few blocks away. NB it is in a night life area so you may not be able to park directly on the street the hotel is located on if you try to park on a weekend night. However there is plenty of street parking nearby and within walking distance.Also if you visit the City's tourist office located in the old firehouse on the square before you register, you will get a discount booklet which, when we visited, had a coupon from the hotel with a 3 nights for the price of two deal.All in all a good value. 
