<Content>so many hassles so little time arrived 4 a.m. after being completely lost in a downtown full of torn up streets, no street signs, hopelessly incorrect maps through help of a good samaritan. I had called and reserved for that time but no room! After some discussion (in Spanish with night man) I walked around the area but nothing available. Went back, told him I would sleep in car and then expect room in the morning. Suddenly a room was available (but only for a few hours), OK by me. In morning they moved me to a room with a wall AC that was so loud I couldn't even hear the TV. Finally the second night I complained and was moved to a room with cardboard walls and smell of cigarette smoke from next room.  They did not charge for the first night and I thanked them for that, but then they wanted each night paid....no paying at check out! Freezer outside in dark to get your ice, chip it out of a block. Park your car a few blocks away or hope to find a place on the street. No internet connections, a coffee pot and some cookies on the counter for continental breakfast.  It was a traditional old hotel, kept very clean which was about the only positive thing I can think of. I thought for the price it was a rip-off. 
