<Author>Chlie
<Content>Saved our Vacation!!! My wife and I had booked a room in Cabo Rojo. The room proved to be the biggest mistake of our vacation. We did try to tough it out there, but decided during our sleepless night that we would be leaving in the morning. We were determined to find a place to stay and made our way to Ponce. We were lucky to have found Hotel Belgica. It is in the heart of Ponce and offers very convenient access to the beautiful attractions that Ponce has to offer. We chose a windowless room on the advice of one of the employees to avoid the noise of the nightlife. The room was very clean and the staff was very polite and helpful in getting around the town. We will definitely keep Hotel Belgica in mind on our next trip to Puerto Rico.A good tip before you decide to do ANYTHING. Take the trolley tour for $2.00 offered at the Fire House. With the tour, you get a coupon book with tons of great offers. We visited the Museum de Ponce BEFORE we took the tour. The coupon book had a nice discount for visiting the museum. Not only do you get the savings book, the tour itself is more than worth the price of admission. The tour is given in both Spanish and English. The trolley stops at a sports museum, observes one of the oldest and biggest trees in Ponce, and stops at a Cemetery which has been converted into a museum due to its historical significance. One trip on the trolley does not do it justice. It is a must see attraction on any vacation to Ponce. 
