<Author>babylovestravel
<Content>Very clean, comfortable hotel with more charm than Ponce itself We had a room with a king sized bed and a balcony, which was a bit noisy at night with the traffic below. However, the room was large and nicely furnished. The high ceilings and original details were lovely. The bathroom seemed recently renovated and spotlessly clean. The bed was comfortable, lighting pleasant, a/c quiet and effective. I highly recommend the hotel, but not Ponce. The Lonely Planet guidebook we had was very misleading. We planned two nights there, but left after one. There was only one restaurant open for dinner. We walked and walked looking for someplace to eat breakfast, and the only place we could find was a food counter in a store. The center square was mostly deserted except for a few drunks, and was mostly just bare dirt around the trees. Only a couple of the buildings around it were nice. All in all, Ponce had a depressed and deserted feeling to it. 
