<Content>Super friendly, charming hotel. Full of character. Old tiles, nice staircase, windows with wooden doors, funny fake flowers everywhere.. The owner meet us at the counter, walked out the door of his hotel and help us find street parking (not that easy midday). Told us all the places to go. Very central location. The rooms were old world basic and nice. We had a balcony, lots of hot water, very high ceilings, air conditioning, and a water cooler in the hall. Finally felt like we were in a different country. Ponce is very attractive. I prefered this value hotel over the hotels I visited around the plaza. Two of use stayed for $65. $50 less than the other hotels. Service was very helpful. He told us all the exhibits in the area, gave us maps, where to find good reasonible food and restaurants all over town. Even if the owner hadn't given us such first class treatment the hotel has old world charm without being contrived. 
