<Author>ILfemale
<Content>Friendy and Unique I stayed at the Hotel Belgica during my first trip to Puerto Rico last month. The Hotel was hard to locate based on the on-line directions we were given, but once we found it we were relieved to have a pleasant stay. The staff is very friendly, and eager to learn more English from mainland US natives. They asked us to park in a spot on the street where they could keep an eye on our car, and gave us an extra mattress for a member of our party without extra charge.Both the lobby and rooms have lots of character and charm. The lobby is covered on all sides with large ornate mirrors, and the very high ceilings in the rooms make the rooms almost as high as they are wide.The rooms opening to the front balconies do not have windows -- but that is ok; it makes it easier to sleep in without the morning light peaking through.I did see one roach in the bathroom, but had no other cleanliness issues with this hotel. We were even given washcloths upon request -- a rarity in Puerto Rico, we found! 
